# Day 01 - Project Initialization

**Date:** 26 June 2026

## 🎯 Goal

Initialize the CloudShift AI project and establish a professional project structure before starting development.

---

## ✅ Tasks Completed

* Created the GitHub repository for CloudShift AI.
* Created the IntelliJ Maven project using Java 26.
* Initialized the Git repository.
* Configured the `.gitignore` file.
* Created the initial project folder structure.
* Added project documentation folders.
* Prepared the project for future development.

---

## 📚 Concepts Learned

* Why professional projects should have proper documentation from Day 1.
* Importance of Git version control and maintaining a clean commit history.
* Repository organization for long-term scalability.
* Difference between project setup and feature implementation.

---

## 🤔 Decisions Made

* Java 26 will be used for development.
* Maven will be used as the build tool.
* GitHub will be used as the central repository.
* The project will evolve incrementally from a monolith to a cloud-native SaaS platform.
* Every new technology (Docker, Kafka, Terraform, Kubernetes, AI) will be introduced only when the application requires it.

---

## 🚀 Next Steps

* Design the business requirements.
* Create the database model.
* Define REST APIs.
* Set up the Spring Boot application.
* Start implementing authentication.

---

## 💡 Reflection

Today was focused on building a strong foundation rather than writing business logic. A well-structured repository, clear documentation, and version control will make future development easier and better reflect professional software engineering practices.
